                            <comment id="13239281" author="ash211" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 07:37:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13244677" author="thepaul" created="Mon, 2 Apr 2012 21:36:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would argue that Archlinux is the broken one, in this respect: nearly everything executable in the Python ecosystem still expects an unqualified &quot;python&quot; to be python2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But oh well. This is an easy improvement to make. The logic in the original patch is backward; you want sys.exit to exit with False when the version is good (since False becomes 0, which shell treats as success). Adjusted a little for brevity and inverted logic.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13244923" author="ash211@gmail.com" created="Tue, 3 Apr 2012 02:14:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Paul&apos;s patch looks good to me, and I agree that python being a python3&lt;br/&gt;
is nonstandard. An easy fix to support though, and flipping the error&lt;br/&gt;
code is right too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anything else needed before applying the patch to trunk?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;

